                     as the expectation of a random quantity. Therefore, it is not possible for a contract enforcer (e.g., judge) to infer perfectly which project had been chosen just by looking at the realization of the final cash flow. Alternatively, we could have explicitly added a noise term, which would have added to the algebra but not aided the intuition.

